 :tx/rationale "Create task: SOUND-C8: Move DDIS-specific methodology scoring to policy layer. CONTEXT: methodology.rs (1,396 LOC) in braid-kernel contains DDIS-specific hardcoded logic: INV/ADR/NEG category detection, spec language pattern matching (contains 'INV-' or 'ADR-'), methodology scoring that assumes the DDIS ontology. guidance.rs lines 2706+ have ISP projection weights hardcoded for Intent/Spec/Impl. C8 says: 'The braid kernel must not contain logic specific to any programming language, test framework, specification format, or project methodology — including DDIS itself.' Test: 'would methodology.rs make sense for a React project with Jest and Jira?' No. RATIONALE: C8 is a hard constraint. Every C8 violation makes braid less general and harder to adopt for non-DDIS domains. The fix is straightforward: policy.rs already exists for policy manifest weights. Move methodology-specific patterns there. APPROACH: (1) Identify all DDIS-specific patterns in methodology.rs: spec_language detection (INV-/ADR-/NEG- prefixes), category weights, methodology component definitions. (2) Move these patterns into the policy manifest as data: :policy/spec-language-patterns (list of regex patterns), :policy/methodology-weights (map of component→weight), :policy/ontology-categories (list of recognized category keywords). (3) Modify telemetry_from_store() to read patterns from the store's policy manifest instead of hardcoded strings. (4) Provide a default DDIS policy manifest (already exists in bootstrap.rs) that includes the INV/ADR/NEG patterns. (5) Non-DDIS projects would provide a different manifest with different patterns. (6) Similarly for guidance.rs ISP weights: read from policy, not hardcoded. ACCEPTANCE: (A) No DDIS-specific string literals remain in methodology.rs or guidance.rs kernel code. (B) All patterns come from policy manifest datoms. (C) Default DDIS manifest preserves current behavior (no regression). (D) A test creates a store with a non-DDIS policy manifest and verifies methodology scoring works with different patterns. (E) C8 test: 'would this kernel code work for a React project?' passes by construction. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/methodology.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/policy.rs. TRACES-TO: C8 (substrate independence), INV-FOUNDATION-006."
